Businesses closed early in Marsabit Town after the Friday shooting incident. [Betty Njeru, Standard]  Three people sustained gunshot wounds at Kiwanja Ndege in Saku Sub-County, Marsabit County on Friday evening after two unknown gunmen raided their home.  The attackers arrived at the victims’ home on a motorbike and opened fire, seriously injuring the three, who were taken to Marsabit County Referral Hospital for treatment.  Marsabit Deputy County Commissioner David Saruni told The Standard that the victims – an elderly man, a middle-aged woman and a child – are members of one family.  Businesses were forced to close early on Friday as tension remained high in Marsabit Town.  Leaders want security beefed up in Marsabit  Marsabit conflict has worrying traits of genocide in the making  Marsabit clash victims buried as politicians warned  State sends security reinforcement to Samburu, Marsabit to quell violence A relative calm, however, resumed on Saturday morning, with traders opening shops for business.   New Cancer Centre opens in Marsabit town, it will offer screening for breast and cervical cancer  Uhalifu Marsabit: Hali ya taharuki inashuhudiwa kufuatia kuuawa kwa wau wawili na mifugo kuibwa  Peace meeting underway in Laikipia County, to seek peace in Marsabit County By Rashid Lorogoi | 9 hours ago By Mate Tongola | 2 days ago By Lucas Ngasike | 3 days ago By Jacob Ng’etich | 5 days ago Escaped convicts sat under trees and told us they were charcoal men